Lonmin said on Monday it narrowed its first-half operating loss and lowered its spending target for the year as the platinum miner prepared for a merger with Sibanye-Stillwater, The London-listed miner, which is being bought by Sibanye-Stillwater, reported a first-half operating loss of $32-million compared with a loss of $181-million a year earlier. It lowered its full year capital expenditure target to 1.2-billion to 1.3-billion rand ($98-million-$106-million) from 1.4-billion to 1.5-billion.